Silver Standard Resources Inc Revenue and Financial Data

   Silver Standard Resources is developing silver mining projects throughout the Americas. Most of its assets are in silver -- it controls proved and probable silver reserves of about 285 million ounces -- with the rest in by-product metals such as gold, tin, and zinc. The company owns and operates the Pirquitas mine in Jujuy, Argentina, which is one of the largest primary silver mines in the world. It also has projects in Canada, Chile, Mexico, Peru, and the US. Also, Silver Standard has a partnership with Minco Silver to explore silver projects in China. In 2013 the firm agreed to sell its San Agustin project in Mexico to Argonaut Gold for approximately $75 million to fund future exploration.
  







